			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It's that time again I guess, to try to make sense from the multitude of rash and sometimes quite insane posts on this forum.. In the past I've made many new ideas to further our class, and this time is no different.  My goal is provide the building blocks for unique spells or abilities that aren't just rehashed watered down versions other classes have.. While some may indeed look like other class spells, they have a special magician flare to them .. This thread will have no roots, no snares, no slows and no charms.  Im sorry if you want those, in consolation I suggest you make an Enchanter and go to <a href="http://www.castersrealm.com" target="_blank">www.castersrealm.com</a> <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
To Absor if you read this - I've made many valuable contributions to this board and the class, and I will always try to provide balanced ideas so I hope you read these and I fully allow Sony to take any part of them for further use.  That is enough for me to see unique abilities grace EQ again <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
As we come upon the dawn of a new expansion we ask ourselves, what do Mages really want or need? Well what we want are those things I mentioned would not be mentioned, what we need is a different manner.  Having played EQ for such a long time as a Magician I've come to realize a few things that we have been denied for no good reason, since in the past year or more the dividing lines between other classes have broken down yet ours remain.
<br />

<br />
Spells
<br />

<br />
There arent too many of them yet, as Im only dealing with new spells and  I fully expect upgrades to nukes so Im not even gonna list them
<br />

<br />
Here is a link to my previous post
<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=7166" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=7166</a>
<br />

<br />
Blade Shield - Summoning forth a multitude of interlocking swords the Magician is able to create a barrier that protects them both from physical and magicial attacks.  In addition any melee attacker suffers damage from the very nature of attacking a spinning swarm of blades.
<br />
Increase Absorb Damage by 650
<br />
Increase Damage Shield by 150
<br />
Mana Cost: 300
<br />
Skill: Conjuration
<br />
Casting Time: 5
<br />
Target: Self
<br />
Duration: 1 hour
<br />
Classes: MAG 64
<br />

<br />
Barrier of Steel - Projecting forth a magicial metallic wall the Magician is able to prevent a certain amount of melee damage from reaching him, at the expense of losing concentration thus not being able to regenerate mana as quickly.
<br />
Absorb Melee damage 50%
<br />
Max damage absorbed 1200
<br />
Decrease Mana by 10
<br />
Mana: 200
<br />
Skill: Conjuration
<br />
Cast Time: 4
<br />
Recast Time: 30
<br />
Target: Self
<br />
Duration: 30 minutes
<br />
Regeant: Pearl
<br />
Classes: MAG 62
<br />

<br />
Absorb Fire - A mystical shield which would absorb a certain amount of fire damage before dissapating, similar absorbs would be given to other casters but only one could be active at a time
<br />
Absorb and Negate 3 Spells
<br />
Limit: Fire
<br />
Mana: 100
<br />
Skill: Abjuration
<br />
Casting Time: 3
<br />
Recast Time: 60
<br />
Target: Self
<br />
Duration: 5 minutes
<br />
Classes: MAG 60, WIZ 60
<br />

<br />
Now those spells may not really be completely unique, but I think they have a certain amount of Mageness in them .. And being self only they wouldn't be overly powerful.  However that isn't what I spent most of my time thinking on, the new AAs for pets is what I've been trying to come up with and here is my first draft.. Keep in mind I am NOT after the universal boosting of magician power, I believe in balance not simply buffing us so these abilities do have drawbacks as you will see
<br />

<br />
A new form of specialization in Alternate Advancement 
<br />

<br />
Elemental Attunements
<br />
Cost - 9 Points each and may be purchased at levels 62, 63, 64, 65 (or whatever the new level caps might be, so just transfer those into post 65).  You may only choose 1 of the following, and 1 additional with each level of Harmony of the Elements
<br />

<br />
Earth - Your earth pets have substanially more HP and do more damage, however your air pets do less damage and have less HP.  Elemental Form Earth has it's bonuses increased by 50% but you may not use Elemental Form: Air
<br />

<br />
Water - Your water pets do a substanial amount of extra damage, including backstabs and have a lowered delay.  The bonus' from Elemental Form: Water are doubled.  You may not use Elemental Form: Fire and all your other pets do less damage and have less hp
<br />

<br />
Air - Your Air pets do more melee damage and are granted a more powerful stun effect.  Elemental Form: Air grants resistances of 15/25/40.  You may not use Elemental Form: Earth and all your earth pets do less damage and have less hp
<br />

<br />
Fire - Your fire pets have their mana regeneration rates dramatically improved and they  have more hp.  Elemental Form: Fire has its bonus' doubled.  You may not use Elemental Form: Water. 
<br />

<br />
Harmony of the Elements - 4/8 Points -  Through careful balance of the elements you have learned to master a previously learned Attunement.  When this ability is taken the disadvantages to pets associated with your previously learned Attunement are negated, however the penalties to opposite aligned Elemental:Forms remain.  You may take this ability twice, once at level 63 and again at 65.  Also each level allows you to take an additional Elemental Attunement, so you may have a maximum of 3 attunements. 
<br />

<br />
So thats all nice and dandy but Im sure you're wondering how would this even work? Benefits, disadvantages? The way I have it working is this.  They would be activatable abilities which would have a refresh of 1 second and leave a hidden effect on you much like mod rods do and would last for 6 hours, not sure yet on that.  During this time you would be unable to use another Attunement and all the detrimental effects of that attunement would last for the duration, so it would be in no way permenant (Like improved relcaim).  So if you use Attunement Earth you would be unable to use elemental form: air for the duration, even with Harmony of the Elements.  
<br />

<br />
The KEY POINT in attunements is to allow the Magician to form a bond with the particular element of pets they like the most and recieve bonuses for that pet, and in a roleplayish sense your attunement towards a particular element would be so taxing you would lose focus in the other 3, unless you get Harmony of the Elements.  My first thought was to make this change permenant but I thought no no we learned out lesson from improved reclaim right? So I came up with this new improved way, but I didn't wanna make it trivial so 6 hours would last for a group or a raid and then after that you could choose something else.  Also you can choose NOT to use an attunement thus retaining your normal pets, this would allow Magicians more variety in choices for pets IMO and give us pet bonuses on a non-universal scale..
<br />

<br />
Oh yeah one last thing about the water attunement.  Yes the disadvantages are rather large but since it is such a high DPS pet, vs a lower one like earth or air I determined the disadvantages needed to be higher
<br />

<br />
I welcome any constructive ideas <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><br>
<br />
<img border=0 src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg" />
<br />
