				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I figured it wouldnt as popular because of the downside.. But in order to get spells sometimes they need to have a downside.. Thats balance, if its too good we'll never get it
<br />

<br />
Virtually every good spell in EQ has a downside, aggro or mana, a component or something else
<br />

<br />
Its all about balance, as I said at the beginning of the thread its not about giving us extremely powerful spells but ones that make sense ..
<br />

<br />
Without some kind of detriment the spells would need to cost a lot more mana, cause more aggro or have a more expensive component.. The wall spell would be used primiarly on raids where mana regen is not even an issue, you need to remember the context.  You wouldnt use it during soloing generally, and even so its more of a situation spell .. The rune you would have up all the time
<br />

<br />
Its hard to really explain balance to those who want everything heh.. About the Attunements tho.  Yes you shouldnt lose power by gaining power, but you're not.. Again its in the name of balance.  If there were no downside to the attunements they would have virtually no power to them as I believe Sony would never give us another "Freebie" focus item.. Therefore with a high AA point cost to stabilize the downside (You need to read further) and if you choose 3 attunements you would never get rid of all of the downsides, you can justify the gain in power.. Try to look past simply buffing our class, it has to work with all the other classes and you simply cannot give one class more power without either buffing every class or putting in a downside...
<br />

<br />
IMO it is the best way to get a bonus.. These downsides are hardly that bad, would you prefer no benefit and no downside? That's probably what we'd get instead heh<br />_________________<br /><br>
<br />
<img border=0 src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg" />
