				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">New Spells:
<br />

<br />
Name: Napalm
<br />

<br />
Decrease hps by 1050.
<br />

<br />
Mana Cost: 800
<br />
Casting Time: 8 sec
<br />
Recast Time: 12 sec
<br />
Target Type: Single
<br />
Resist Type: Fire
<br />

<br />
Lands 3 quick pulse direct damage spells on the target for 1050 damage each.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Was thinking about something like this on the way home from work the other day, it would make a cool effect because the DDs land back to back quickly unlike the rains. So the effect would be BOOM! BOOM! BOOM! really fast. More of a "fun thing" rather than overly useful    <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" />    Of course it wouldn't have the stupid resist check like rains either.
<br />

<br />
New AAs:
<br />

<br />
Pet Sacrifice:
<br />

<br />
AA cost: 9
<br />
Levels: 1/1
<br />
Reuse Timer: 2min
<br />

<br />
This AA grants the magician the ability to sacrifice his pet with no mana regain but leaves a corpse for the magician to reclaim any tradeable items equipped on the pet. Of course if the pet dies or is killed by any other means all equipped items are lost.
<br />

<br />
One advantage mages have over other pet classes is equipping our pets with summoned items, how about letting us extend on that by reclaiming items so we can make use of other items like the serrated bone dirk.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=705852" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Nucci</a>
<br />
<a href="http://pub58.ezboard.com/bsoldiersofvalor77770" target="_blank" class="postlink">Soldiers of Valor</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
