				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We have 4 different pets for a reason, though that reason is being blurred with the fire pet still be used very infrequently, but putting that aside. To choose at anytime in the game to make one pet better by aaxp points and that is locked in steel is wrong. Your favorite pet of today you choose to upgrade may not be the one you want if another expansion comes out after you choose. Example, they change the fire pet again and you chose air for instance. Now the fire pet is very usable, large mana pool, won't melee and is the perfect raid pet per say. You raid often would want this pet, but too late, you already decided. Lets say you take the water pet, but again they change the air pets stun to last longer and upped it's ac to be better, focused by the AAXP's you used on water pet, but alas sorry you chose already the air pet.
<br />

<br />
It should be as we have 4 pets you max any new aaxp's that increases the power of that type of pet you get the bonus, spend enough points and you can max the one you want, when you summon it.
<br />

<br />
Mages are the only class with  different pets, just think if they added aaxp points like that to Necro's and BL's they have 1 type of pet, they can't choose wrong, they would ALWAYS have the best pet, while we would suffer. Sorry, anything dealing with pets should be across the board for all pets, may take time to max them all, but all should be able to be maxed.
<br />

<br />
As for spells having a down side? Shielding line has no down side, Solar Vortex has no down side, black steel no down side, call of hero, pets, and pet buffs etc.. no down sides with any of our spells that I can see. If you want to say well our damage spells causes aggro as down side I think your reaching. None of our benifical spells have a downside. Your shield for mages suggestion is like a rune skin (and the Enchanter version in PoP take NO reagants, and has ZERO downside to it). Sorry I don't see spells like that having a downside, a necro FD can fail, but their rune skin once up won't fail. This would the mage equivalant of rune skin for us. Why have it lose 10 mana a tick on us? Sorry still don't and will never buy the argument that you have to have a negative side effect on a useful spell. Mana cost is the price you pay for casting the spell, fizzles we all can have happen etc.. just don't like and never did like a built in penalty for a benifical spell. 
<br />

<br />
Calebe</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
