I was atracted to the mage class way back in 99 by this ability.  
<br />

<br />
Give us useful summons.  Somthing that would drop of a mob of the same lvl as the spells it.  No Rent is a downside, and a good balancing factor.  Its downside and balacing factors have long been overlooked by all.  
<br />

<br />
Most classes that get the increases by thier own buff can at the end of the night.  Buff themselves, then do their banking selling etc reclaiming some of the mana, and med to the rest right before they camp.  The still have time left on their buffs.  No rent mean you have the overhead of summoning all this stuff BEFORE you start your day in EQ.
<br />

<br />
Buff our pets all lvls through changing the current lower level summong spells to mean something.  
<br />

<br />
Buff us at lower to mid levels the same way.  
<br />

