				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some spur of the moment AA ideas:
<br />

<br />
Planar Bindings
<br />
3/6/9
<br />

<br />
10/25/50% chance for a mob's summon to fail. For balance, maybe add in a (very) short duration root to show how the summon is stopped because your bound in place... I dunno.
<br />

<br />
Resplendant Elemental
<br />
6
<br />

<br />
Summons an elemental with the hps of a SoAS focused Rathe's Son, with a "phantom" mana cost of 600 (phantom because its an AA skill and doesnt take mana). The pet would have a ton of hps, but would hit like the level 4 fire pet. Useful only for pet canni, in which case it improves pet canni for people with and without IRE. Oh... and obviously everything would be reduced because it is an AA skill and really doesnt have a mana cost... just reduce the hps and the "phantom" mana cost. Normal pet cast time.
<br />

<br />
Some final ideas...
<br />

<br />
Echo of the Rathe/Echo of Ro/Echo of Marr/Echo of Xegony
<br />
Summons a psuedo pet that lasts for a minute or so and, while summoned, has a song effect that increased hps/damage shield/healing/ac. Have multiple levels to increase the duration and maybe turn it into an AE ability? Just brainstorming.
<br />

<br />
And the idea for a pet rune that summones your suspended pet when you get hit... I want it.<br />_________________<br />Archangyl, 65 Arch Convoker
<br />
Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
