				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Elemental Blast line (Type) of spells  Maybe starting at 34 or 39 and have several going up to 65.
<br />

<br />
This line of spells has 4 compenents (Parts) for the 4 elements we can call forth as our pets.
<br />

<br />
Its 1 part fire nuke.  (Fire pet)
<br />
1 Part Cold Nuke      (Water Pet)
<br />
1 part magic nuke     (Earth Pet)
<br />
and 1 part stun.        (Air Pet)
<br />

<br />
or conversly
<br />

<br />
1 part fire nuke    (Fire pet)
<br />
1 part cold nuke   (Water Pet)
<br />
1 part magic nuke (Air Pet)
<br />
1 part disease or poison nuke (Earth Pet)
<br />

<br />
Each part has is own resists, so on say a fire immune MoB  the other three parts can still hit.
<br />

<br />
Depending on the version I would say the lvl 65 spell in the line would do 600 per type for the all nuke, or 800 for the three nuke + stun.  2400 shouldn't be too overpowering espcially since most mob have a high resistence in one of those area it would end up being more like 1600 to 1800 damage.  Not overpowering, but unique.  Mana ratio should be comparatable to or slightly better than our current nukes, but less mana efficent that wizzy's.
<br />

<br />
Another unique spell could be both a buff and a bane spell.  
<br />

<br />
The spell of modulation.  would have three spells.  One for each of our rod's + a Higher one.
<br />

<br />
This would be a very unique spell in that it would work on both PC's and on MoB's   Single target and do dasically what our Mod Rod's / Trans Rod's do to a greater extent.  Needless to say it would be unresistable
<br />

<br />
the 44 Version would cost 150 mana and trade the target 300 HP for 175 mana.
<br />

<br />
The 56 Version wouls cost 200 mana and trade the tartget 500 HP for 275 mana
<br />

<br />
The 63 Version would cost 450 mana and trade 800 hp for 500 mana
<br />

<br />
Or  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />  We could have a line of modulate spells that take HP from the target and give us the mana.  Same unresistable type of spell.
<br />

<br />
Same ratios as above.  Would be great on raids to help deplete the mana of the High end mobs, and would give us better role in the raids.  The ratio's may need some adjusting, but Because we do not have the intermediary step of the summoned item, they should return more mana than they cost.
<br />

<br />

<br />
What do ya think...<br />_________________<br />Elawise Fyremountain</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
